;; lab-review-learns.glitch — glitch reviews the same PR three times with increasing context
;;
;; Pass 1: cold review — just the diff
;; Pass 2: diff + reviewer feedback from pass 1's mistakes
;; Pass 3: diff + all prior rounds — shows learning
;;
;; Target: prometheus/prometheus#18531 — smoothSeries @ modifier bug
;;
;; Run with: glitch run lab-review-learns

(workflow "lab-review-learns"
  :description "Three-pass PR review — glitch learns from feedback each round"

  ;; ── Fetch PR data ───────────────────────────────────

  (step "fetch-pr"
    (run "gh pr view 18531 -R prometheus/prometheus --json title,body,files"))

  (step "fetch-diff"
    (run "gh pr diff 18531 -R prometheus/prometheus"))

  (step "fetch-reviews"
    (run "gh api repos/prometheus/prometheus/pulls/18531/reviews --jq '.[].body'"))

  (step "fetch-comments"
    (run "gh api repos/prometheus/prometheus/pulls/18531/comments --jq '.[] | \"FILE: \" + .path + \"\\nLINE: \" + (.line|tostring) + \"\\n\" + .body + \"\\n---\"'"))

  ;; ── Pass 1: Cold review — diff only ─────────────────

  (step "review-cold"
    (llm
      :provider "copilot"
      :model "sonnet"
      :prompt ```
        You are a senior Go engineer reviewing a Prometheus pull request.
        You have ONLY the diff. No discussion, no reviewer feedback.

        Review for:
        1. Correctness — does the fix actually solve the stated problem?
        2. Edge cases — what inputs could still break?
        3. Test coverage — are the tests sufficient?
        4. Missed issues — anything the author didn't address?

        Be specific. Reference file names and line numbers.

        PR metadata:
        ~(step fetch-pr)

        Diff:
        ~(step fetch-diff)
        ```))

  ;; ── Pass 2: Informed — cold review + real reviewer feedback ──

  (step "review-informed"
    (llm
      :provider "copilot"
      :model "sonnet"
      :prompt ```
        You are a senior Go engineer reviewing a Prometheus pull request.
        You have the diff AND feedback from a previous review pass.

        A previous reviewer (you, in an earlier pass) wrote this review:

        --- PREVIOUS REVIEW ---
        ~(step review-cold)
        --- END PREVIOUS REVIEW ---

        Now here is what the ACTUAL maintainer reviewers said:

        --- MAINTAINER REVIEWS ---
        ~(step fetch-reviews)
        --- END MAINTAINER REVIEWS ---

        --- INLINE REVIEW COMMENTS ---
        ~(step fetch-comments)
        --- END INLINE COMMENTS ---

        Compare your previous review to the maintainer feedback.
        What did you get right? What did you miss? What did the
        maintainers catch that you didn't?

        Now write an IMPROVED review incorporating everything you
        learned. Be specific about what changed in your assessment.

        Structure your response as:
        ## What I missed
        (list what the maintainer feedback taught you)

        ## Improved review
        (your corrected, more thorough review)
        ```))

  ;; ── Pass 3: Full context — all prior rounds ─────────

  (step "review-full"
    (llm
      :provider "copilot"
      :model "sonnet"
      :prompt ```
        You are a senior Go engineer on your THIRD review pass of a
        Prometheus pull request. You have everything:

        - The diff
        - Your cold review (pass 1)
        - The maintainer feedback
        - Your improved review (pass 2)

        --- PASS 1 (cold) ---
        ~(step review-cold)
        --- END PASS 1 ---

        --- MAINTAINER FEEDBACK ---
        ~(step fetch-reviews)

        ~(step fetch-comments)
        --- END MAINTAINER FEEDBACK ---

        --- PASS 2 (informed) ---
        ~(step review-informed)
        --- END PASS 2 ---

        --- DIFF ---
        ~(step fetch-diff)
        --- END DIFF ---

        Write your FINAL review. This should be your best work —
        informed by two prior passes and real maintainer feedback.

        Then write a self-assessment:
        ## Final review
        (your definitive review)

        ## Self-assessment
        Rate each pass (1-10) on:
        - Correctness of analysis
        - Edge cases identified
        - Actionable feedback quality
        - Alignment with maintainer perspective

        Show the scores as a table.
        ```))

  ;; ── Assemble lab page ───────────────────────────────

  (step "write-lab"
    (llm
      :provider "copilot"
      :model "sonnet"
      :format "json"
      :prompt ```
        Write a lab case study showing how glitch improves its PR review
        quality across three passes on the same pull request.

        VOICE: Write for dev architects evaluating glitch. Direct, technical,
        no hype. Show the real output, let quality speak for itself.

        Output a JSON object (no markdown fence):
        {
          "slug": "review-learns-prometheus",
          "title": "Learning to Review: Three Passes on the Same PR",
          "description": "glitch reviews prometheus/prometheus#18531 three times — cold, with feedback, then with full context. Watch the review quality improve.",
          "date": "2026-04-18",
          "content": "<markdown>"
        }

        IMPORTANT: Keep the content CONCISE. No more than 200 lines of markdown.
        Summarize model output — do NOT dump raw responses. Use short quotes
        (1-3 sentences) to illustrate key points. Use tables for comparisons.

        The "content" field structure:

        ## The PR
        One paragraph describing prometheus/prometheus#18531. Link to it.
        What was the bug, what was the fix.

        ## Pass 1: Cold Review
        2-3 sentence summary of what the cold review found.
        One short quote showing what it got right.
        One short quote showing what it missed.

        ## What the Maintainers Actually Said
        2-3 sentence summary of the real reviewer feedback.
        The key insight the maintainers caught.

        ## Pass 2: Informed Review
        2-3 sentences on how the review improved.
        What it learned from the feedback. One short quote.

        ## Pass 3: Full Context
        2-3 sentences on the final review quality.
        One short quote showing the improvement.

        ## Score Progression
        Use the self-assessment table from pass 3.

        ## Takeaway
        2-3 sentences on iterative review with accumulated context.

        RAW DATA:

        PR:
        ~(step fetch-pr)

        PASS 1:
        ~(step review-cold)

        MAINTAINER REVIEWS:
        ~(step fetch-reviews)

        MAINTAINER COMMENTS:
        ~(step fetch-comments)

        PASS 2:
        ~(step review-informed)

        PASS 3:
        ~(step review-full)
        ```))

  ;; ── Save ────────────────────────────────────────────

  (step "save-lab"
    (save "site/generated/labs/review-learns-prometheus.json" :from "write-lab"))

  (step "done"
    (run "echo 'Lab generated. Run: glitch run site --set action=sync to publish.'")))
